<refentry id="baselib-setstate-r-1">

<refmeta>
<refentrytitle>setstate_r</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Base Libraries</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>setstate_r</refname>
<refpurpose>reentrantly change the state array used by random number generator functions</refpurpose>
<indexterm id="ix-baselib-setstate-r-1">
	<primary>setstate_r</primary></indexterm>
</refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv>
<funcsynopsis>
<funcsynopsisinfo>
#include &lt;stdlib.h&gt;
</funcsynopsisinfo><funcprototype>
<funcdef>int
<function>setstate_r</function>
</funcdef>
<paramdef>char *
<parameter>statebuf</parameter>
</paramdef>
<paramdef>struct random_data *
<parameter>buf</parameter>
</paramdef>

</funcprototype>
</funcsynopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1>
<title>Description</title>
<para>
The interface <function>setstate_r</function> shall function in the same
way as the interface <function>setstate</function>, except that
<function>setstate_r</function> shall
use the data in
<parameter>statebuf</parameter> instead of the global random 
number generator state.
</para>
</refsect1>
</refentry>
